article.description: Ryan Ross ran for 149 yards and two touchdowns, Daniel Sams ran for another score and McNeese State beat Southeastern Louisiana 21-7 on Saturday.
article.headline: McNeese State downs Southeastern Louisiana 21-7
article.story: LAKE CHARLES, La. -- Ryan Ross ran for 149 yards and two touchdowns, Daniel Sams ran for another score and McNeese State beat Southeastern Louisiana 21-7 on Saturday. With the Southland Conference's top-rated defense, the Cowboys (5-0, 4-0) held the Lions (3-2, 2-1) to 59 yards rushing and forced two fumbles while generating 369 yards of total offense. Sams scored on a 3-yard run on McNeese State's opening drive and Ross scored on a 58-yarder on the second drive for a 14-0 Cowboys lead. The Lions struck back when D'Shaie Landor hit William French with a 54-yard pass and a personal foul penalty moved the ball to the McNeese State 1-yard line. Xavier Roberson ran it in on the next play. Ross gave the Cowboys a 21-7 halftime lead after a 4-yard TD run and had rushed for more than 100 yards before the intermission. He finished with 15 carries.
